## TEM Panel Reference — IIS, FMS, and AWC Panels

### IIS and Web Tier Panels

| Panel | Fields | Validated values |
|-------|--------|-----------------|
| `WebTierIISPanel` | Use existing site, use existing app pool, virtual directory name | Existing site, dedicated pool, `tc` |
| `DefaultSiteWebServerPanel` | Host, Port, Application Name | `server2019tc`, `80`, `tc` |
| `MidtierServersPanel` | 4-tier server URI list, gzip | `http://server2019tc/tc`, gzip enabled |

Configuration categories in `configuration.xml`:
- `existWebSiteName`, `webSitePort`, `webAppName`, `webAppPoolName`, `webTierUrl`, `tcAppPath`

---

### FMS and Cache Panels

| Panel | Fields | Guidance |
|-------|--------|---------|
| `FscServerPanel` | Server ID, Address, FSC Group, Server Type | Define FSC roles if FMS topology is in scope |
| `FccDefaultsPanel` | Windows Cache Directory, Max cache sizes | Keep under a user-resolvable local path, e.g., `$HOME\FCCCache` |
| `FscConnectionsPanel` | FSC service URLs and ports | Current gateway config references FSC bootstrap URL `http://server2019tc:4544` |

Configuration categories: `FSCServiceFCCDefaults`, `FSCServiceConnections`, `FSCService`, `FSCMasterSettings`, `filerepo`

---

### Active Workspace and Microservice Panels

| Panel | Fields | Guidance |
|-------|--------|---------|
| `AwsCorporateServerPanel` | Search Engine URL | Use Solr URL: `http://server2019tc:8983/solr` |
| `GatewayServicePanel` | Gateway Service Port, Active Workspace URL, Node.js path | Port `3000`; if using system Node.js, document the exact path |
| `MicroservicesWinPanel` | Master/worker node, keystore, Service Dispatcher port, Service Registry port | Master node first; Service Dispatcher default `9090`, Service Registry default `8787` |

Current gateway on this host:
- Gateway port: `3000`
- Gateway `/tc` target: `http://server2019tc/tc`

Configuration categories: `microservices`, `registryPort`, `dispatcherPort`, `gatewayPort`, `gatewayPort`

---

### Optional Supporting Panels

These may appear depending on selected features. Do not guess if you see them — stop and verify the feature is intentional:

`FTSPanel`, `FtsIndexerClientSettingsPanel`, `ReadExpressionPanel`, `ArtifactServicePanel`,
`OfficeOnlineMicroservicePanel`, `OdataServicePanel`, `DataProxyPanel`, `DatabaseDaemonsPanel`,
`TcCS*` panels, `Volume*` panels, `TransService*` panels
